.SH PLegendre_d1
Compute all the unnormalized Legendre polynomials and first derivatives.
.SH Usage
call PLegendre_d1 (\f[CR]p\f[R], \f[CR]dp\f[R], \f[CR]lmax\f[R],
\f[CR]z\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]p\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
An array of unnormalized Legendre polynomials up to degree
\f[CR]lmax\f[R].
Degree \f[CR]l\f[R] corresponds to array index \f[CR]l\f[R]+1.
.TP
\f[CR]dp\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
An array of the first derivatives of the unnormalized Legendre
polynomials up to degree \f[CR]lmax\f[R].
Degree \f[CR]l\f[R] corresponds to array index \f[CR]l\f[R]+1.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum degree of the Legendre polynomials to be computed.
.TP
\f[CR]z\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The argument of the Legendre polynomial.
.TP
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R] : output, optional, integer(int32)
If present, instead of executing a STOP when an error is encountered,
the variable exitstatus will be returned describing the error.
0 = No errors; 1 = Improper dimensions of input array; 2 = Improper
bounds for input variable; 3 = Error allocating memory; 4 = File IO
error.
.SH Description
\f[CR]PLegendre_d1\f[R] will calculate all of the unnormalized Legendre
polynomials and first derivatives up to degree \f[CR]lmax\f[R] for a
given argument.
These are calculated using a standard three\-term recursion formula, and
the integral of the Legendre polynomials over the interval [\-1, 1] is
\f[CR]2/(2l+1)\f[R].
Note that the derivative of the Legendre polynomials is calculated with
respect to its arguement \f[CR]z\f[R], and not latitude or colatitude.
If \f[CR]z=cos(theta)\f[R], where \f[CR]theta\f[R] is the colatitude,
then it is only necessary to multiply \f[CR]dp\f[R] by
\f[CR]\-sin(theta)\f[R] to obtain the derivative with respect to
\f[CR]theta\f[R].
